What I want editing experience to be like:
- I want to be able to configure special rules for special types, e.g. (72 line width on commit and readme)
- I want to have some help with formatting, and I want to apply it differently depending on project
- I don't want the formatter to completely change for example how I align stuff, e.g. comments, arrays, etc. for any language
- I prefer to code with 8 tabs regardless of language, but I don't want that to impact the files themselves, I want to view a file differently from how it should be stored. How it should be stored should be according to formatting settings
- I'm thinking about not auto format on save, but maybe format on keybind?
- Maybe make my prefered fileview option a togglable state. So that I can view the file for what it is, and then i can do <leader>+SOMETHING which turns it into 8 indent tabs, etc?
